<br>
<br>
&quot;Alteration<br>
Another of the several skills related to the art of magic, alteration deals with changing things, whether it is illusion or an actual physical change. An example would be a spell that teleports something, or that enables a character to move faster, or forces him or her to move more slowly.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Conjuration<br>
Another of the several skills related to the art of magic, conjuration brings something from elsewhere into the world, whether they are elemental creatures or powerful clouds of energy.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Key Words:<br>
&quot;Alteration ~~An example would be a spell that teleports something...&quot;<br>
&quot;Conjuration ~~ conjuration brings something from elsewhere into the world&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Sorry man, but when you cause person A to move from point B to point C, you are using alteration, you are NOT using conjuration. You are not bringing something magical from elsewhere into the world, person A was ALREADY in the world.<br>
<br>
